post_text:
Students across the country are expressing how distance learning is working for them. Many students who at one time complained about getting out of bed to go to school, the bell schedule, and constant due dates, now realize that there was a sense of responsibility in doing those things. They have also expressed the social network that a school site enables on a daily basis. I encourage our students to continue to do their best at home by making a daily schedule and sticking to it as much as possible. This Wednesday we are also beginning our Wednesday Wellness Workouts. I will facilitate a short workout session for staff and students at 9 a.m. for Meadowlark, 9:30 a.m. for High Desert, and 10 a.m. for Vasquez High School. I hope to see and connect with many students and staff that I‚Äôve missed seeing in school!
#aadusdstaygold #actonschooldistrict #aadusd #gohawks #gomeadowlarks #gomustangs #firesidechat

post_text:
There has been a lot of discussion about activities that normally happen during this time of the school year. In particular, seniors want to know about the prom, graduation, grad night, and so on. These are traditions, celebrations, and the rewards of working so hard throughout our students‚Äô K-12 years. I am here to support our VHS principal, Mr. Brockway and our other site administrators to ensure these activities become a reality in one form or another. If that means events are delayed until we can do them ‚Äúlive‚Äù then that‚Äôs an option. At this point, all options are on the table. We want our seniors and all of our students to have a memorable and valuable end of year experiences regardless of the current situation. We are all Mustangs! #aadusd #actonschooldistrict #aadusdstaygold #weareallmustangs #firesidechat #gomustangs

Larry King

AADUSD Supertintendent

LA County Library Offers Temporary Digital Library Card
Customers Can Access eResources, Including eBooks, Movie Streaming, and Online Classes

Due to COVID-19 precautions, all of LA County Library‚Äôs 86 locations are currently closed to the public through March 31, 2020. Due dates for borrowed materials have been automatically extended, no late fines will be assessed, and customers can return materials when the Library reopens.

In an effort to make access to all of the Library‚Äôs digital resources more easily available to Los Angeles County residents, including those who do not currently have a library card, LA County Library is offering a temporary digital card, valid for 90 days. To sign up for a temporary digital card, LA County residents can visit LACountyLibrary.org/library-cards.

‚Ä¢ All pledges and payments are made online* at

donation amount for students.
‚Ä¢ Students will average 26-36 laps The maximum laps
counted is 36 and each lap is 1/16th of a mile.

post_text: Good morning. This is the Acton-Agua Dulce Unified School District. Today, Wednesday, October 30, 2019, all school sites will be closed due to power outage. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. We are monitoring the situation and it is likely power will be out tomorrow, Thursday, October 31, 2019. Friday is already scheduled as a non-student day. We will send another message out tomorrow morning if the power is not restored. As always, the safety of our students and staff remains our highest priority. Thank you for your patience.
text: Good morning. This is the Acton-Agua Dulce Unified School District. Today, Wednesday, October 30, 2019, all school sites will be closed due to power outage. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. We are monitoring the situation and it is likely power will be out tomorrow, Thursday, October 31, 2019. Friday is already scheduled as a non-student day. We will send another message out tomorrow morning if the power is not restored. As always, the safety of our students and staff remains our highest priority. Thank you for your patience.

post_text: All 3 of our schools will be closed tomorrow, Tuesday, October 29, 2019, due to maintenance. We want to be sure the air quality in all of our classrooms are safe for students and staff. Our sites‚Äô centralized air conditioning and heating climate control systems were impacted by the nearby fires. Although our sites may or may not lose power tomorrow, we are closing schools for health and safety which is the District‚Äôs first priority. Moving forward we will continue to inform you the morning of the day we are not in operation. When SCE informs the District that the power may be out, we inspect our sites at approximately 5 a.m. If there is no power, then we announce that school is closed. This is the process we will return to on Wednesday and Thursday. It is possible that we will not have power on those days as well, due to high winds. Thank you for your patience. And again, all sites will be closed tomorrow, Tuesday, October 29.

post_text: Today, Friday, October 25, all 3 of our schools will be closed. A number of our employees have had to evacuate their homes who reside in the SCV. Additionally, several of our families who live in Agua Dulce have also been impacted. At this time, our hearts go out to our Santa Clarita Valley neighbors who are having to contend with fires, poor air quality, and transportation issues. As always, our first concern is the safety and well being of our students and staff. Thank you for your patience and understanding.

post_text:
The Acton Agua Dulce Unified School District is pleased to announce that we will begin using the Raptor Visitor Management System in all of our schools to strengthen our program of campus safety for students and faculty, The Raptor system will go into effect prior to Oct. 1st, 2019.

The Raptor Visitor Management System scans the ID's of those wishing to gain access to a school. It will log the name of the visitor as well as the date, time and purpose of the visit. It will also compare the name and date of birth with the registered sex offender database, and will alert school
staff when there is a match.

post_text:
The resignation of a Board Member created a vacancy for the Board of Trustees.

The Board of Trustees at the Special Board meeting on Friday, July 26th, has determined to proceed by appointing a provisional member.

Please complete and return to the Acton-Agua Dulce Unified School District office by Monday, August 5, 2019, no later than 4:00 p.m. Applicants must be 18 years of age or older, a citizen of the State of California, a resident of the school district, a registered voter, and not legally disqualified from holding office (Ed. Code 35107).

Applicants will be interviewed during open session at a Special Board of Trustees meeting, date to be determined; this meeting will begin at 6:00 p.m. Applications are considered public record and a copy of your application may be requested by the press.

Please visit the district website to print out the required information sheet.

post_text: Superintendent, Mr. King was invited for the second consecutive year by our teacher‚Äôs association to attend the 5th Annual Innovation in Education Conference in Arcadia. It is a one day conference that truly inspires educators. I was joined by Nicole Chun (4th grade teacher), Melissa Trussel (5th grade teacher), Alexa Lepp (5th grade teacher), Ted Pelham (5th grade teacher), Lisa Simonian (Dean), and NIcole Salcedo (VHS counselor). The keynote speaker, Katie Martin, instructional coach, mentor, and educator, was amazing. Her mantra is: ‚ÄúWhen we tell kids to complete an assignment, we get compliance, but when we empower kids to explore and learn how to make an impact on the world, we inspire innovators.‚Äù It was very powerful to hear her speak.

Ribbon cutting ceremony on Saturday May 11th was a great moment for our students, parents and community. The phase III sports complex has been completed!

The Board of Trustees, Superintendent, Mr. King and VHS Principal, Mr. Dan Andrus dedicated the softball field to Mr. Larry H. Layton. The scissors used to cut the ribbon were presented to Mr. Layton's granddaughter, Alanna Layton.

post_text:
Proclamation on Peace Officers Memorial Day and Police Week 2019!

On Peace Officers Memorial Day and throughout Police Week, we express our unending gratitude to our Nation's law enforcement officers. Those brave men and women selflessly confront danger to protect our families and defend our communities. We also honor those in blue who have been killed or disabled in the line of duty. We are especially mindful of the tremendous sacrifices of the 106 heroes who laid down their lives last year while protecting their communities! We humbly THANK YOU!

Our school district is updating its Local Control Accountability Plan (LCAP) for the 2019-2020 school year. The State of California requires school districts to write goals and actions to address eight state mandated priority areas. We seek your input in this annual process.

Thank you for taking this survey and providing us your feedback regarding the schools in our district.

Gratefully,

Acton-Agua Dulce Unified School District

The District would like to congratulate Candice Palacios on being selected as Teacher Ambassador for DonorsChoose.org.
Ms. Palacios was awarded a Stay Gold Coin and received a Stay Gold certificate from Superintendent, Mr. King. We were so excited that a video was set up for her husband to be able to watch his wife receive these accolades. Mrs. Palacios's husband is currently overseas on deployment (Air Force).
